      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img width="1024" height="576" src="https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?fit=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-rss-image-size size-rss-image-size wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?w=1920&amp;ssl=1 1920w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=1536%2C864&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=1200%2C675&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=780%2C439&amp;ssl=1 780w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=400%2C225&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?resize=706%2C397&amp;ssl=1 706w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/leapmotor-d19.png?fit=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1&amp;w=370 370w" sizes="(max-width: 34.9rem) calc(100vw - 2rem), (max-width: 53rem) calc(8 * (100vw / 12)), (min-width: 53rem) calc(6 * (100vw / 12)), 100vw" /></figure>
<p>Chinese EV maker Leapmotor unveiled its flagship D19 SUV on Wednesday evening, the first model built on its new high-end D platform. The vehicle will be available in both pure electric and range extender variants.</p>



<p>The pure electric D19 features a 115kWh battery offering up to 720km range, 1000V fast charging that adds 350km in 15 minutes, and a maximum output of 540kW. The range extender version pairs a generator with dual motors, cutting system weight by over 60kg and providing 500km pure-electric range with an 80.3kWh battery and 40L fuel tank.</p>



<p>Both versions feature advanced technologies such as Qualcomm dual 8797 chips with 1,280 TOPS AI computing power for in-cabin AI models and driver assistance, as well as LMC2.0 chassis control, DLP projection headlights, and a 60-inch AR-HUD. The company has not yet announced pricing. [TechNode reporting]</p>
]]></content:encoded>
