<p>Redmi has unveiled the K90 Pro Max, its first smartphone to carry the “Pro Max” name, expanding the brand’s flagship K series. The device features a “Flowing Gold White” finish, large rounded corners, ultra-narrow bezels, and a unibody metal “volcanic” camera housing. Next to the camera sits a large speaker labeled “Sound by Bose,” marking the first collaboration between Redmi and the audio brand.</p>



<p>According to Xiaomi executive Lu Weibing, the K90 Pro Max will target the RMB 4,000 (about $550) price segment and represents a major upgrade in the lineup. The model is positioned as Redmi’s top-tier offering within its performance-oriented K series. [TechNode reporting]</p>
