      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img width="1024" height="510" src="https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?fit=1024%2C510&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-rss-image-size size-rss-image-size wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?w=1039&amp;ssl=1 1039w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=300%2C149&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=768%2C382&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=1024%2C510&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=780%2C388&amp;ssl=1 780w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=400%2C199&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?resize=706%2C351&amp;ssl=1 706w, https://i0.wp.com/technode.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/duckov.jpg?fit=1024%2C510&amp;ssl=1&amp;w=370 370w" sizes="(max-width: 34.9rem) calc(100vw - 2rem), (max-width: 53rem) calc(8 * (100vw / 12)), (min-width: 53rem) calc(6 * (100vw / 12)), 100vw" /></figure>
<p>Bilibili Games has published <em>Escape from Duckov</em>, a top-down single-player extraction shooter set on an absurd cartoon “Duckov Planet.” Developed by its in-house studio Team Soda, the PC title is priced at RMB 58 in China and $17.99 in the US, with a 12% launch discount available until Oct. 29.</p>



<p>Marketed as a “survival comedy,” the game places players on a collapsing duck world where they must scavenge, fight, and build a spaceship before planetary destruction. It supports 10 languages, including Simplified and Traditional Chinese, English, and Japanese, and is available on Steam, WeGame, Epic Games Store, Bilibili Game Center, and Mac App Store. [TechNode reporting]</p>
]]></content:encoded>
